bilingual.target: 而且这个价格符合我的预算。

bilingual.source: The price of those pencils is pretty high.
bilingual.target: 那些铅笔的价格相当高。

bilingual.source: The price of the fruit depends on its size.
bilingual.target: 这种水果的价格取决于它的大小。

bilingual.source: Ali bought a new computer game despite the price.
bilingual.target: 尽管价格昂贵，阿里还是买了一个新的电脑游戏。

list.abstract: price是一个英语单词，有价格、价值等意思。

yingyinNormal.en: In fact it's not a price. We don't think of zero having any down side. We don't think of it as having a price.
yingyinNormal.zh: 事实上不算是价格，我们认为它没有任何负面影响，我们不认为它是个价格。

yingyinNormal.en: I already have. And for twice the price, thanks to you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我已经卖了，还是以两倍的价格，这得感谢你。

yingyinNormal.en: And it even influences the kind of price we are willing to pay for coffee at home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 甚至于我们居家时喝的咖啡的价格。

yingyinNormal.en: They basically want to tell us that whatever we learned from Dunkin' Donuts, whatever historical presence for price was, was now irrelevant.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们想透露的是我们所知道的邓肯甜甜圈的价格以及过去物品的价格都与他们毫无关系。

yingyinNormal.en: People who paid discounted price for the same cough medications didn't feel as well.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然而那些付了折扣价格的人，虽然接受了同样的治疗但是感觉并不好。

yingyinNormal.en: When the price of something rises, people will supply more of it and buy less of it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当某种东西的价格上升，人们自然会增加生产，然后买的人就会变少。

yingyinNormal.en: I asked Bear Stearns to price our shorts. They tell me the CDOs still haven't moved.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我让贝尔斯登给我们的做空估个价，他们告诉我担保债务凭证的价格没变。

yingyinNormal.en: One way to think about the anchors is that it's the first time we encounter a price, it's the first time we think about the particular decision, and that way of thinking about the decision sticks with us for a long time.
yingyinNormal.zh: “锚”其实是指我们第一次遇见的价格，第一次思考并作出决定购买的价格，往后会长时间影响我们。

yingyinNormal.en: But discount to zero is particularly influential, it's particularly be, because zero is a different price.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是折扣到零影响力更大，真是的是这样，但是0是个不一般的价格。

yingyinNormal.en: Friendship and loyalty are for the weak. Let everyone know I'll cook another batch. And raise the price up to $3.00.
yingyinNormal.zh: 友谊和忠诚只属于弱者，通知大伙我会再出一批松饼，价格涨到三块钱。

yingyinNormal.en: He was attempting to sell trade secrets to a competitor. If the suit drags on, it could hang over the stock price.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他试图将公司交易机密卖给竞争对手。如果这个官司拖得太久，可能会影响到股票价格。

yingyinNormal.en: Not a child? A child's coffin would be more expensive. This is in the lower price range, although still best available in that bracket.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是孩童吗？孩童的棺材会更贵。这种价格较低。不过也是同档次中最好的。

yingyinNormal.en: So in some sense we are self might be creative despite the price cure the relationships rather than having it be a part of the reality.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从某种意义上讲是因为我们内心的期望尽管价格也会产生影响但期望才是主要原因

yingyinNormal.en: But it's an antique. Is it? Daddy says it's worth lots of money. Well, I never. I'd better put the price up. Bye.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可是这把椅子是古董。是吗？爸爸说这个古董很值钱的。我都不知道，我要提高价格了。再见。

yingyinNormal.en: Juror number seven. You think because he's gay he'll hate that I represent a firm that was accused of price gouging AIDS medication.
yingyinNormal.zh: 7号陪审员，你觉得他是同性恋，所以会因为我代理一家哄抬艾滋病药物价格的公司而反感我。

yingyinNormal.en: So one winter, we asked students to keep track of the medications they took, the price they paid, and how well they felt afterwards.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在某一个冬天，我们让学生们逐笔记录他们所选择的治疗，他们支付的价格，以及治疗之后的感觉。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, so when I got a fine for leaving my clothes in the dryer for too long, that was from you? $14.99. The exact price of a new gavel.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以上次我把衣服留在烘干机太久收到了一张罚单，那是你开的吗？14.99元。正是购买新木槌的价格。

yingyinNormal.en: If someone charges less than you, customers will buy from them instead. So you have to lower the price or offer something better.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果有个人贩卖的价格比你低，那么顾客自然会去向他们买东西。所以你必须要降低售价，或是提升产品的质量。

yingyinNormal.en: Ten years later when we all used to thinking about the coffee in a completely new domain, in a completely new approach, in a completely new price range, they don't need to pretend to be different any more.
yingyinNormal.zh: 十年之后，当我们都偏向于以这种新视角新工艺新价格去看待咖啡时，星巴克也就不需要再假装与众不同了。

yingyinNormal.en: A price paid in lives taken.
yingyinNormal.zh: 代价就是夺走一切生命。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 股价；股票价格；股票行市

examination_example.sentence: Until this century, university libraries were not very <highlight>price</highlight> sensitive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到本世纪，大学图书馆对价格都不是很敏感。

examination_example.sentence: Likewise, automation should eventually boost productivity, stimulate demand by driving down <highlight>prices</highlight>, and free workers from hard, boring work.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同样，自动化最终应能提高生产力，通过压低价格刺激需求，并将工人从辛苦、枯燥的工作中解放出来。

examination_example.sentence: Upcoming reforms might bring the <highlight>price</highlight> to a more reasonable level.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 即将到来的改革可能会使价格更加合理。

examination_example.sentence: On the other hand, putting your faith in the wrong place often carries a high <highlight>price</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一方面，把你的信念放在错误的地方，往往要付出高昂的代价。

word_usage.usage: price作名词，表示“价格；价钱”时，通常与动词go up或rise搭配，表示“价格上涨”，与fall或drop搭配，表示“价格下跌”。
price作及物动词，其后可直接接名词或者代词，如：price various travel packages 为各种旅行套餐定价。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 表示“价格；定价；价钱”，主要指卖主给商品定的价格，一般都高于成本，也引申为做某事而付出的代价。
表示“成本；费用；价钱”，多指对要价的支付。
表示“费用；价钱”，指卖主或服务者为自己的服务或商品索要的价钱、报酬。
表示“费用；花费；开支”，常指为某物实际支付的金额总数，也可指各种花费，指金钱，也可包括时间、精力等。

derivative_info_list.mean: adj. 贵重的；无价的；无法估价的；稀世之珍的；极为有趣的；极为可笑的

word_family.mean: n. 价格；价钱；（Price）人名：普赖斯

examination_example.sentence: Grass fed milk can fetch up to times the <highlight>price</highlight> of conventional milk.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 草饲牛奶的价格可以达到传统牛奶的好几倍。

examination_example.sentence: This is partly driven by the rising <highlight>price</highlight> of raw materials and metals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 原材料和金属价格的上涨在一定程度上促使企业开始行动。

examination_example.sentence: Retail <highlight>prices</highlight> for a handful of tomatoes at local markets have risen from $0.50 to $2.50.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当地市场上番茄的零售价格从0.50美元上涨至2.50美元。

examination_example.sentence: There is always a <highlight>price</highlight> to pay to develop technology for a better world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了更美好的世界而开发技术，总是要付出代价的。

word_usage.usage:
“价格的上涨”用动词go up或 rise，“价格的下跌”用fall或drop。
示例：(1) House prices rose/went up again. 
房价又上涨了。
(2) They believe that the price will fall/drop.
他们认为价格会下降。

price一般与high或low搭配表示“价格的高低”，不能用cheap或expensive。
示例：这家商店的鞋价钱很便宜。
误 The price of shoes in this shop is cheap.
正 The price of shoes in this shop is low.

询问“价钱”一般应该说what price或how much (money)，不能用how much price。
示例：那件衣服你要卖多少钱?
误 How much price do you charge for that dress?
正 How much do you charge for that dress?
正 What price do you charge for that dress?

examination_example.sentence: They charged a high <highlight>price</highlight> for their space-roasted coffee beans.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的太空烘焙的咖啡豆要价很高。

examination_example.sentence: She still remembers the sting of her first experience skipping an assignment due to the high <highlight>prices</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她至今还记得第一次因为高价而逃掉任务所经历的痛苦。

examination_example.sentence: The codes — which typically range in <highlight>price</highlight> from $ 80 to $ 155 per course — give students online access to systems developed by education companies like McGraw Hill and Pearson.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 代码(通常每门课程的价格从80美元到155美元不等)使学生可以在线访问由麦格·劳希尔(McGraw Hill)和皮尔森(Pearson)等教育公司开发的系统。

examination_example.sentence: Lower-<highlight>priced</highlight> goods attract more customers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 低价商品会吸引更多的顾客。

examination_example.sentence: Why is the medium soda <highlight>priced</highlight> the way it is?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为什么中杯汽水如此定价？

examination_example.sentence: Each Friday night a truck came, with cases of food that had to be unloaded, <highlight>priced</highlight>, and placed on shelves.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每周五晚上都会有一辆卡车来，装载着需要卸货、定价和上架的食品。

examination_example.sentence: They don't give any consideration to the <highlight>price</highlight> their comfort has paid for the environment and consequently for themselves.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们从不考虑他们的舒适对环境甚至对自己的代价。

examination_example.sentence: Hunters willingly pay the stamp <highlight>price</highlight> to ensure the survival of our natural resources.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 狩猎者都愿意支付印花税，以确保我们的自然资源能够维持下去。

examination_example.sentence: Their <highlight>prices</highlight> may climb up as time passes.

examination_example.sentence: It's sold at a discount <highlight>price</highlight>.

word_usage.usage:
当询问某物的价格时，我们用“What's the price of...?或How much is...?”提出问题，而不是说“How many/much price…?”。说价格的高或低时，用high或low与price搭配，expensive和cheap表示商品的贵贱，不与price搭配。请看下列例句：
①Fuel oils are expensive now.
②The prices of fuel oils are high now.
③I can't sell it at as low a price as he asked.
